On Thu, Feb 14, 2008 at 01:53:15PM -0800, Harvey Harrison wrote:
> In C, signed 1-bit bitfields can only take the values 0 and -1, only
> 0 and 1 are ever assigned in current code.  Make them unsigned
> bitfields.
> 
